< text>
Nice park to go to. Really big and has two playgrounds for the kiddos. It has skating ramp for the kids to take their bikes skateboard or scooters. For the big kids or experienced skaters and the other for smaller kids or less experienced skaters. Bathrooms are clean. Baseball field and sidewalk to jog or walk and just lots to explore. My kids always have fun here.< /text>

<userid>105900223873134443088</userid><username>Stephen J. Lautenschlager<//username><Time>1558212586507</Time><rating>4< /rating>< Review>
The Temecula Skate Park is a very good location for recreational scooter, skateboard and inline rollerskating.  The park consists of a competition 60-foot diameter bowl with ramp entry. A 10-foot wide apron connects the upper bowl with a street plaza skate area. The street plaza has a pyramid, fun box, curbs, ramps, stairs, and a handrail. The facility is lighted for night skating.< /Review>

Went to the park and the first thing I noticed were the employees giving me attitude. I rented out some pads and was told to put them on in front of them. Right when I got in, I noticed how weirdly the park was set up. I could tell most of the park hasn't even been touched yet because of where they're located. After I got done skating, I took off the pads and realized that whole area was red and itchy. My arms and knees smelled horrible, like they don't even take care of their equipment. Overall that skatepark is horrible. I was only there for 45 minutes before I became sick of the park. The employees also kept yelling at me to put my helmet back on when I'm either standing up scratching my head or sitting down taking a breather. The park is filled with scooter kids and their moms watching over them from outside. I never went back since.<//Text>

<Text>I have been taking my kids to this Park for about a year and they love it.  It is not what I would call an advanced level park, but its a great Park for kids and entry to intermediate skaters and Pro Scootering.  They do require that you wear a helmet and pads, which is smart.  And they only charge $1 for a year membership to the park which gives you supervision over your kids.

In reading some other peoples comments I want to first give you the history and probably where they are coming from because this park is not open 24 hours a day, which it could and probably should be.  However, some kids have been injured here, as they are at every skating park because its part of the sport, yet the parents tried to sue the city.  So thanks to them this park will more than likely never be open 24/7.

As for someone mentioning money.  Seriously dude!  Its $1 for a year membership.  If you can't afford that then I suggest you get a job and/or a clue.  This park is losing money and could easily charge the going rates which are $5 to $10 for a 2 hour session.

And for the rental equipment, my kids now have there own because they are really getting into the sport, but as for your comment on getting a rash because the equipment it dirty and not cleaned.  My kids never had a problem and used their equipment for 6 months with no issues.  Also one of the reviews on this park cites a specific incident claiming of this rash which is NOT TRUE because in the post it states that they made him put the pads on to go SKATING, and he did not like the park because it was filled with SCOOTER kids and their moms.  This park holds separate skate sessions for skate boarders and scooter, which is a park rule, so that posting is not true.

Also some of the negative comments here are more than likely from BMX Bikers that are angry because this park does not allow them to use the facility.  So over time many of them have vandalized the park, tried cutting the fence and locks, and trying to give this place bad reviews.  Don't take it out on the workers take it up with the city!  And maybe if you tried diplomacy vs vandalism the city might just listen.  You may not know this but the city was going to recently allow BMX Bikers back into the park, but then when the city fixed the holes in the fence they saw several BMX Bikers cutting through the fence again so they brought this up at the last city counsel meeting and now your ban continues from the park.

Also I believe the employees are extremely friendly and caring about the kids!  I am not sure about people saying bad things about them because they have a genuine love and care for all the kids.</Text>< UserId.>

Great, quaint space! Outdoor seating was the best part about this "roadhouse." Food was over priced for what it was but I'll attribute that to the location. Welcome to Big Sur where we will overcharge you for everything. Food was average at best. Fries were greasy. $14 for a turkey BLT. $3 for an 8 oz bottle of diet coke.....really? <Date>1566402158406</Date>< Rating>

< Review>
While the food tasted good, it was over priced and the attitude from the staff was atrocious. We were driving back north from Julia Pfeiffer SP, and I made my husband drive out of our way past Big Sur SP because this place caught my eye.  It was a snap decision and I did not read the reviews about the rude service. If I had, we would have just gone to one of the other restaurants along this stretch of highway 1.

The girl taking orders and then bringing the food out seemed highly bothered to be doing her job. She was rude and very abrupt with us. We had ordered a lemonade for my daughter, and after paying was told they don't have lemonade and the alternative offered was a very small bottle of apple juice (which was WAY over priced at $3.50). The apple juice, as over priced as it was, cost less than the lemonade I had already paid for and no effort was made to reconcile the difference or apologize that I did not get the product I paid for. I learned my lesson about tipping at the time of ordering instead of at the end of the meal. I would have never left anything close to the tip I gave had I paid at the end of my meal.< /Review>

<text>A cool looking place from the road but I would not go back!  A beautiful back patio with stunning views over the forest- could be a very lovely place but this is a place where you must serve yourself completely.  I initially sat on the front patio but there seemed no interest from inside to anyone on the patio know you had to order inside.  There were 3 people and there dog who arrived before me and when they went inside and di not come back out I realised I needed to go inside to seek service.   As soon as I walked in with my 2 well-behaved dogs I was greeted by a gentleman behind the counter who told me they welcomed dogs on the front and back patio but not inside.  I started to make my way to the back patio and he told me the only menu was on the chalkboard inside.  It was clear from his comment he wanted me on one of the patios with my dogs and when I asked if he had a menu I could take with me he said no - -fortunately a co-worker piped up and said it was OK for me to have the dogs whilst I ordered.  (Mind you this is a counter with no seating and the restaurant portion of the inside was not in the vicinity of the counter).

The back patio was beautiful and the food was decent.  The place advertises fresh ingredients but the avocado was the spreadable costco style.  The food was good otherwise and the view was good - I guess in spite of acting dog-friendly when I was first greeted this is really not a dog-friendly place (or at least not by this staff member) and on top of that - -I didn't even get a glass of water or offered a drink with my meal.

The decent breakfast and the great back patio view are the only reasons this review is not a 1 star.  This is the worst stop in my 3 years of vacationing in Carmel area with my dogs and I will never stop here again!!</text><Pictures>None<//Pictures><response>None<//response>< gmapID>

Excellent service!  I got a tire repaired here. I pulled in with NY plates and a sharp stone through a fairly new tire.  It took much longer than I expected as I assumed it would be a easy plug job.  The stone did too much damage to be that easily repaired.  The mechanics removed the tire and repaired it from inside with a patch for larger holes.  Even though I was quoted 10 dollars for the repair,  I expected to, and would have understood if I had to pay more. The bill was exactly as quoted and the repair was top notch.  I travel back and forth between Corning, Ca, and Corning, NY and I appreciate quality.  I will bring all of my repair work while in the west to Corning Auto Center from now on.</Review>

<Review>I'm driving south on I-5 in my motorhome and notice the engine check light is on.  I stopped in Corning, CA. good for me. I had two codes and the one they found right away the mice had eaten into my coil wire and it my have caused the second code. But the tech new it was a reach to think it was the problem with the second code. He went back and took a second look and found an injector wire the mice had got to, that was the second code. 1</rating>
< text>
We bought a new air conditioning/heating unit last year for over $10,000 and are supposed to have a semi annual inspection of it to check to make sure everything is working. Their guy shows up with an attitude goes into our attic and claims we have a tear in the vents and it is not covered under our warranty. He said he say a mouse trap and when I asked if there was any droppings, he said no. We told him that the trap as been up there since we bought the home 5 years ago and that the picture of the damage was a clean tear, such with a knife. No bite marks at all. My husband and I told hem that the only people that have been in the attic is from Monarch, so either he did it today or the last guy that game 6 months ago did it. However, he is the only one that came with an attitude.

After telling us this he kept asking us if he wanted him to continue with his service and we kept saying do what you are supposed to do. He asked us two more times if we still wanted him to finish his service and we kept telling him yes. When he came down from the attic to show us the picture of the tear in the vent you can see that the tear was done with something sharp, like a knife. No rodent bites anywhere. We asked the service guy to call his supervisor, but he refused and instead held up his phone so I could have his number. I called him to let him know what is going on, of course I am upset, and the first thing he says is what does your contract say and to that I replied, isn't that your job to look up, for which he replies "CALM DOWN" which I wasn't yelling, cussing or even anything but being upset and he hangs up on me.

Now I have been waiting for days for supposedly the District Manager and then the General Manager to call me but with no success. I wait two days and call yet again and talk to another person that says she will look into this and make sure we didn't already have this tear. Amazing that when you tell a company that only they have ever been in your attic, they treat you like a criminal.

Please note, they are really nice for the initial sale and then they want more, more, more money for things you may not need and to fix things they will do to you.

My advise, hide a camera up there so you can film them.

Good luck!!
Marcia</text>

< review>
DO NOT USE THEM FOR AIR CONDITIONING !!!!!

I am so disappointed with Monarch. Initially I was trying to contract my reliable service company Coleman of California, which serviced our unit bi-yearly, summer & winter but was connected to a toll number who had a Monarch rep. When I questioned if this was indeed Coleman of California, they tried to confuse me by saying yes we service for them, upon questioning them about the history of my unit, I quickly determined it was not the same company but later they finally admitted they bought out Coleman of California,. ( which translate we picked up their accounts).
I had been satisfied with the previous company so I had them send a tech since my ac was not cooling down. Long story short the first tech could barley make it from the van to my door without stopping for water, but made it to the roof, to tell us our capacitor went out to the blower, he replaced it charged a service & parts fee and checked the air for a few minutes, collected his check. After a very short time within 1 hour we noticed it was not cooling again. They sent our a different repair tech very late in the day, who tells us the first tech should of replaced the blower motor at the same time and would discount the cost of the capacitor and charge for the Blower Motor now. Since then I contacted the Manager Mark Dupree, who offered a free year service.
Unfortunately it has only been 2 months and the ac is NOT working, upon this visit, we're told the Fan Motor is fried and will cost $1000.00 to repair and they suggest a salesman to come over and review the cost of a new one $13,000.'s later, we say , " Thank you "  knowing they thought easy sale, dumb elderly people or whatever.
We have had the repair done by another A/C company referred by our reputable contractor whom we used for 30+ yrs. They were able to repair the problem informing us that, it is a old unit and will need more repairs but replacing will cost 1/3 of Monarch's price.  LESSON LEARNED...
The one star only is given because they showed up....
Alacia R.<//review>
